Re: Could I ask you a favor?
by becki_kanou » Sun 10.03.2010 10:08 pm I thought that might be the reason. It seems that some perfectly good advice for writing: i.e. "Don't OVERuse passives because they can make your writing sound limp" has been reinterpreted as "Don't use passives EVER!", which is just ridiculous. There are plenty of times when passives absolutely SHOULD be used.
