Re: Could I ask you a favor?
by TJack » Tue 10.05.2010 9:30 pm Adverbial conjunctions? Casual clauses? I'm totally lost on some of the words in that paragraph. Your excerpt confused me a little, Hektor6766san ...but I think I get the gist of it. I now remember why grammar lessons always gave me a pain the rear...Does that mean I was basically right though? As long as the "because clause' is complete, the sentence is correct? The following sentence with because doesn't start a noun clause, but just a regular sentence. Because I had a lot of money, I went to Las Vegas.I went to Las Vegas because I had a lot of money.These are both right...right?But a sentence like this:"Because I had a lot of money from my friends." isn't right because it is a sentence fragment. (Thanks Hyperworm, I had a brain fart there! ) Well, off to search for adverbial conjunctions and the like.
